From 1871 through 1946, the Kibune Shrine was officially designated one of the {{nihongo|''Kanpei-chūsha''|官幣中社}}, meaning that it stood in the second rank of government supported shrines. <ref>Ponsonby-Fane, Richard. (1959). ''The Imperial House of Japan,'' pp. 126.</ref>
